  <title>Opportunity International (UK):Sustainable Livelihoods in Nsanje</title>
  <description>This project expands Opportunity International&apos;s existing programme in Malawi which is currently funded by the Scottish Government. The programme to date has been very successful and seen the rapid expansion of microfinance and loan services to thousands of individuals, particularly women, in the northern areas of Mzuzu, Livingstonia and Nkhata Bay. The key outcomes of this next phase will be to provide financial services to at least 17,000 households in the Nsanje District, in the far south of Malawi, in order to increase household incomes, improve livelihoods and improve food security. Key activities will be the establishment of Opportunity International Bank of Malawi branch offices, providing access to microfinance, access to savings accounts, micro-insurance policies and delivering HIV/AIDS training to target groups.</description>
